There are multiple ways to do same, I would prefer doing it with [ReadWriteLock][1]

 **ReadWriteLock**

  

      private ReadWriteLock readWriteLock = new ReentrantReadWriteLock();
        
        @Async(&quot;executor&quot;)
          public void method1(){
          readWriteLock.writeLock().lock();
            // Do somthing
            readWriteLock.writeLock().unlock();
          }
        
          @Async(&quot;executor&quot;)
          public void mehthod2(){
           //lies dormant until the lock has been acquired
           readWriteLock.writeLock().lock();
            // Do something
            readWriteLock.writeLock().unlock();
          }
        
          @Override
          public void run(){
            method1();  // how to ensure that method2 is execute after method1 is over?
            method2();
          }

  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/locks/ReadWriteLock.html

