answers.body_markdown:
It is an invalid function call

    baroncard(choice1, struct gameState *state);
                       ***********************

Instead of an argument you inserted a declaration of the second parameter. You have to use an object of the type `struct gameState *` as an argument the same way as you supplied the first argument.
                       
For example

    struct gameState state;
    //...
    baroncard(choice1, &amp;state);

Or

    struct gameState *state = malloc( sizeof( struct gameState ) );
    //...
    baroncard(choice1, state);

Pay attention to that the name of an object passed as an argument to a function is not necessary must be the same as the name of the corresponding function parameter.

